<i>My menu is all there.</i>

25
00:01:58,959 --> 00:02:01,519
<i>The possibility of getting
served anything else...</i>

26
00:02:01,961 --> 00:02:04,154
<i>as long as it's possible,</i>

27
00:02:04,229 --> 00:02:06,914
<i>my business model.</i>

28
00:02:07,586 --> 00:02:12,951
<i>I am open from midnight
to seven of the morning after.</i>

29
00:02:13,236 --> 00:02:14,311
<i>People call this...</i>

30
00:02:14,417 --> 00:02:17,244
<i>Midnight Restaurant.</i>

31
00:02:17,711 --> 00:02:19,408
<i>How is business doing?!</i>

32
00:02:19,833 --> 00:02:22,778
<i>Well enough, I'd say.</i>

33
00:02:24,386 --> 00:02:27,378
~ SHINYA SHOKUDO ~
Midnight Restaurant

34
00:02:27,378 --> 00:02:32,588
Episode 2
Nekomanma (Cat Food)

35
00:02:37,068 --> 00:02:38,891
<i>The first time she came...</i>

36
00:02:38,937 --> 00:02:42,063
<i>was right around
half past six in the morning,</i>

37
00:02:42,088 --> 00:02:44,881
<i>when I was about to close.</i>

38
00:02:56,719 --> 00:02:59,451
You have katsuobushi*?
(*dried fish scrapings)

39
00:03:00,211 --> 00:03:02,587
I do have it, but...

40
00:03:03,458 --> 00:03:07,715
I wanted some on top of warm rice,
sprinkled with soy sauce.

41
00:03:10,051 --> 00:03:12,063
You mean nekomanma (cat food)?

42
00:03:12,600 --> 00:03:14,717
You like it as well?

43
00:03:14,742 --> 00:03:16,475
Yeah.

44
00:03:21,957 --> 00:03:23,601
Can you...

45
00:03:23,626 --> 00:03:25,537
wait a little while?

46
00:03:25,611 --> 00:03:26,812
Yeah...

47
00:03:26,837 --> 00:03:29,743
I'm a little short on money, though.

48
00:03:29,768 --> 00:03:31,573
Since we're here,

49
00:03:31,598 --> 00:03:34,457
should I make
it from fresh rice?

50
00:03:35,032 --> 00:03:38,256
I suddenly got the
urge to eat some myself.

51
00:03:39,431 --> 00:03:41,113
Really?

52
00:03:41,138 --> 00:03:42,774
Yeah...

53
00:04:48,126 --> 00:04:49,691
Bon apetit.

54
00:05:02,970 --> 00:05:04,439
How is it?

55
00:05:21,109 --> 00:05:23,157
<i>After that day,</i>

56
00:05:23,182 --> 00:05:25,456
<i>and right around the same time...</i>

57
00:05:32,929 --> 00:05:34,054
Hey!

58
00:05:34,903 --> 00:05:37,536
Here I am again.

59
00:05:47,625 --> 00:05:51,244
What is it you do until
this early in the morning?

60
00:05:52,623 --> 00:05:54,442
Is it work?

61
00:05:55,630 --> 00:05:58,004
Karaoke box.

62
00:06:00,371 --> 00:06:02,557
You know...

63
00:06:03,309 --> 00:06:05,198
Promise you won't laugh.

64
00:06:05,249 --> 00:06:06,623
Yeah.

65
00:06:06,816 --> 00:06:10,043
I'm an enka singer.

66
00:06:11,253 --> 00:06:15,840
Although "unsuccessful" should
come before that, I guess.

67
00:06:15,971 --> 00:06:18,760
I get no work,
but I still want to sing,

68
00:06:18,785 --> 00:06:21,135
so I spend the whole
night singing there.

69
00:06:21,160 --> 00:06:22,811
Even though they're not my songs...

70
00:06:23,717 --> 00:06:26,357
Do you have songs
of your own as well?

71
00:06:26,970 --> 00:06:29,053
Just one.

72
00:06:29,124 --> 00:06:30,616
You won't find it
at most karaoke bars,

73
00:06:30,641 --> 00:06:33,106
and nobody really knows about it.

74
00:06:33,556 --> 00:06:35,798
Among our regulars...

75
00:06:35,941 --> 00:06:38,247
there is this composer.

76
00:06:38,483 --> 00:06:39,562
Really?

77
00:06:40,133 --> 00:06:43,059
Bring your poster next time.

78
00:06:43,357 --> 00:06:45,399
I'll hang it there.

79
00:06:45,441 --> 00:06:47,734
Really?

80
00:06:54,387 --> 00:06:56,151
<i>As the day comes to an end,</i>

81
00:06:56,176 --> 00:06:58,956
<i>and people are
rushing back home,</i>

82
00:06:59,193 --> 00:07:02,255
<i>they sometimes
get this uneasy feeling,</i>

83
00:07:02,321 --> 00:07:05,844
<i>getting the urge of spending
the night somewhere else.</i>

84
00:07:09,743 --> 00:07:11,402
Thanks for that.

85
00:07:15,521 --> 00:07:19,887
~ Life, Wherever Fate Leads Me ~
Chidori Miyuki

86
00:07:20,239 --> 00:07:21,919
What's this?

87
00:07:22,988 --> 00:07:26,764
I live to witness this thing here,
now I've seen them all.

88
00:07:28,624 --> 00:07:29,903
Want to buy one?

89
00:07:30,010 --> 00:07:32,258
I even have a CD.

90
00:07:32,319 --> 00:07:34,611
So you've completely fallen for her?!

91
00:07:37,492 --> 00:07:40,924
It's this kiddo who often
comes by to eat nekomanma.

92
00:07:42,241 --> 00:07:44,432
I like it, too.

93
00:07:44,514 --> 00:07:46,088
Nekomanma.

94
00:07:46,173 --> 00:07:47,766
That doesn't sound like
much of an answer, Master.

95
00:07:47,791 --> 00:07:50,333
Does anyone sing "wherever
their fate leads them"?!

96
00:07:50,649 --> 00:07:52,545
I hate that stuff.

97
00:07:52,638 --> 00:07:53,615
What stuff?

98
00:07:53,640 --> 00:07:56,716
You know the stuff they
sing in the southern end?

99
00:07:56,741 --> 00:07:57,427
Of the street?

100
00:07:57,452 --> 00:08:00,170
Yeah...
Who listens to that anyway?

101
00:08:00,636 --> 00:08:03,037
Listening to them
will only make you sad.

102
00:08:03,448 --> 00:08:04,740
Must be the same for her.

103
00:08:05,372 --> 00:08:08,908
But that's where the next
popular star might come from.

104
00:08:08,933 --> 00:08:11,771
Isn't that all the more cruel and sad?

105
00:08:12,320 --> 00:08:15,405
"I might become a
star just like them!"

106
00:08:16,451 --> 00:08:18,871
You know, spreading hope and the like.

107
00:08:19,931 --> 00:08:21,076
Let's listen!

108
00:08:21,101 --> 00:08:23,018
If I like it,
you can sell me one.

109
00:08:23,389 --> 00:08:26,042
All we have here is an old radio.

110
00:08:26,744 --> 00:08:28,174
Sensei...

111
00:08:28,514 --> 00:08:30,151
How about it?

112
00:08:32,434 --> 00:08:34,883
He's a composer, I hear.

113
00:08:35,546 --> 00:08:37,579
The kiddo, does she
come here frequently?

114
00:08:37,609 --> 00:08:40,163
Then, how about you have
her sing here instead?

115
00:08:40,818 --> 00:08:42,170
That's an idea!

116
00:08:42,423 --> 00:08:43,741
Let's do it, let's do it!

117
00:08:43,766 --> 00:08:45,674
If she's good,
I'll buy her CD.

118
00:08:45,785 --> 00:08:48,994
Could become a hit.

119
00:08:50,602 --> 00:08:51,718
This world of ours...

120
00:08:51,743 --> 00:08:54,531
is like the Nile's tide,
what goes around comes around.

121
00:08:54,645 --> 00:08:56,971
Don't belittle life.

122
00:08:58,881 --> 00:09:00,878
Still....

123
00:09:00,903 --> 00:09:05,507
Is he curious to listen
her song or something?

124
00:09:05,532 --> 00:09:06,931
Or maybe he just
wants to meet her?!

125
00:09:06,956 --> 00:09:08,427
When they're young
and breathe, anyone is fine.

126
00:09:08,452 --> 00:09:11,354
- Men are simple, aren't they?
- Yes!

127
00:09:11,379 --> 00:09:13,084
<i>(*rice with green tea and toppings)</i>
Master, another round of ochazuke*.

128
00:09:13,131 --> 00:09:14,600
- Tarako for me.
- Ume. - Salmon.

129
00:09:14,625 --> 00:09:15,657
Coming.

130
00:09:15,813 --> 00:09:18,587
Didn't you say so yourself once?

131
00:09:18,851 --> 00:09:20,633
Time isn't kind
to anyone, darling.

132
00:09:20,658 --> 00:09:24,151
- Like it's kind to you.
- Life, wherever fate leads me?!

133
00:09:25,076 --> 00:09:27,124
Isn't it?

134
00:09:27,951 --> 00:09:31,077
~ Shinjuku Golden Street ~

135
00:09:42,185 --> 00:09:44,350
~ Enka's New Star ~
Chidori Miyuki
CONCERT
~ Free Admission ~

136
00:09:44,375 --> 00:09:49,153
Wherever fate leads me,

137
00:09:49,567 --> 00:09:54,610
wherever fate leads my life to.

138
00:09:55,238 --> 00:09:57,821
From your childhood...

139
00:09:57,850 --> 00:10:00,621
to your adulthood,

140
00:10:00,864 --> 00:10:06,240
life goes wherever
fate leads it to.

141
00:10:06,552 --> 00:10:09,360
Wherever fate leads me,

142
00:10:09,385 --> 00:10:12,178
wherever fate leads my life to.

143
00:10:12,203 --> 00:10:17,548
Wherever fate leads me,
wherever fate leads my life to.

144
00:10:17,814 --> 00:10:20,517
Finding a back alley...

145
00:10:20,673 --> 00:10:23,305
and walking around in circles...

146
00:10:23,464 --> 00:10:28,064
is what I enjoy the most.

147
00:10:29,727 --> 00:10:30,627
I'm buying!

148
00:10:30,652 --> 00:10:32,436
Give me a CD!

149
00:10:32,553 --> 00:10:34,101
Here you go.

150
00:10:40,517 --> 00:10:43,010
Don't know how to explain it,
but it has personality.

151
00:10:43,100 --> 00:10:45,670
Still, your voice makes
quite the impression.

152
00:10:45,853 --> 00:10:51,120
As for the song, I don't really know
whether it's sad or whatever.

153
00:10:51,739 --> 00:10:56,339
But a young lady like you eating
nekomanma, isn't that a little strange?!

154
00:10:56,853 --> 00:10:58,655
You're from the
northeast, aren't you?

155
00:10:58,718 --> 00:10:59,698
How did you know?

156
00:10:59,760 --> 00:11:03,160
Yeah... What they
call nekomanma in the western regions...

157
00:11:03,185 --> 00:11:05,475
is usually rice with soybean paste.

158
00:11:05,612 --> 00:11:08,622
But soy sauce is not too
good for cats' health.

159
00:11:08,941 --> 00:11:10,545
Because it's too salty.

160
00:11:10,617 --> 00:11:12,447
But without soy sauce
it would have no taste.

161
00:11:12,490 --> 00:11:13,555
No, no way.

162
00:11:13,613 --> 00:11:16,444
Because cats have weak
kidneys and don't sweat,

163
00:11:16,469 --> 00:11:17,805
they really don't
need that much salt.

164
00:11:17,945 --> 00:11:19,525
But I love salty foods...

165
00:11:21,659 --> 00:11:24,759
Here... Miyuki-chan.
A present for you.

166
00:11:24,900 --> 00:11:26,990
Why do you always
contradict each other?

167
00:11:27,070 --> 00:11:28,530
Why do you?

168
00:11:28,900 --> 00:11:30,830
Why do we...

169
00:11:30,960 --> 00:11:33,470
If you think about it,
don't you get along just fine?

170
00:11:38,394 --> 00:11:41,024
Stray cat.

171
00:11:41,771 --> 00:11:43,995
Listening to your voice,

172
00:11:44,132 --> 00:11:46,715
the words just came out naturally.

173
00:11:46,825 --> 00:11:48,285
Sensei!

174
00:11:49,124 --> 00:11:50,225
Miyuki-chan.

175
00:11:50,351 --> 00:11:52,381
The most important thing...

176
00:11:52,597 --> 00:11:55,449
is your desire to sing.

177
00:11:55,669 --> 00:11:58,729
Never forget that, all right?

178
00:11:59,595 --> 00:12:01,785
Thank you very much.

179
00:12:16,908 --> 00:12:19,608
Men who cry never return.

180
00:12:19,635 --> 00:12:21,895
A life of wandering filled
her days from the very start.

181
00:12:21,920 --> 00:12:24,067
Once again, a stray cat...

182
00:12:24,153 --> 00:12:26,423
wanders the street
which never sleeps, Shinjuku.

183
00:12:26,840 --> 00:12:29,030
From a back alley far away
from the business quarters,

184
00:12:29,178 --> 00:12:31,518
a woman wandering
the streets in search of a...

185
00:12:31,756 --> 00:12:34,366
blossoming love a man
left withering in the wind.

186
00:12:34,752 --> 00:12:37,195
Where am I headed now?

187
00:12:37,274 --> 00:12:39,904
Here is newcomer Chidori Miyuki,

188
00:12:39,950 --> 00:12:43,300
singing "Stray Cat."

189
00:12:44,047 --> 00:12:54,827
From the lips of a
hostess who no longer knew love,

190
00:12:55,925 --> 00:13:07,735
<i>it listened,
in her lap's embrace.</i>

191
00:13:08,135 --> 00:13:19,927
She sang the old pleas of
men from her past.

192
00:13:20,216 --> 00:13:25,810
Roaming the nights of Shinjuku,

193
00:13:26,021 --> 00:13:30,755
was the stray cat.

194
00:13:30,780 --> 00:13:34,653
Today we feature the hit singer
of "Stray Cat," Chidori Miyuki.

195
00:13:34,743 --> 00:13:37,373
- Welcome.
- Thank you for having me.

196
00:13:44,818 --> 00:13:46,838
~ Chidori Miyuki's "Stray Cat" ~
100,000 Copies Sold

197
00:13:47,041 --> 00:13:57,791
In our fleeting everyday life,

198
00:13:58,950 --> 00:14:03,633
<i>~ Chidori Miyuki - 5 Straight Weeks on Top ~
Sad memories accumulate.</i>

199
00:14:03,633 --> 00:14:09,760
<i>Sad memories accumulate.</i>

200
00:14:10,940 --> 00:14:13,980
Ahh, are you there? Just a moment.
<i>Giving your body and soul...</i>

201
00:14:13,980 --> 00:14:16,940
- He's in the parking lot.
- Yes.
<i>Giving your body and soul...</i>

202
00:14:16,965 --> 00:14:22,541
<i>To a lying man...</i>

203
00:14:23,229 --> 00:14:29,054
I can't really explain it,
but I'm just giving my best for now.
<i>Roaming the streets of Shinjuku</i>

204
00:14:29,054 --> 00:14:34,441
<i>Is the stray cat...</i>

205
00:14:35,065 --> 00:14:35,844
<i>I've gotten used to waiting now</i>

206
00:14:35,844 --> 00:14:39,266
Chidori Miyuki
Entering Red & White Song Contest
<i>I've gotten used to waiting now</i>

207
00:14:39,266 --> 00:14:39,787
<i>I've gotten used to waiting now</i>

208
00:14:39,787 --> 00:14:41,018
- The Red & White Contest!
- She's something.
<i>I've gotten used to waiting now</i>

209
00:14:41,018 --> 00:14:43,035
- The Red & White Contest!
- She's something.
<i>To a woman...</i>

210
00:14:43,035 --> 00:14:46,320
<i>To a woman...</i>

211
00:14:47,052 --> 00:14:58,536
<i>Love is hell even if drenched by the bottle</i>

212
00:14:59,200 --> 00:15:06,808
<i>The wet neon lights glowing in the dark</i>

213
00:16:58,568 --> 00:17:01,943
<i>The very last time she
came to my restaurant...</i>

214
00:17:02,192 --> 00:17:06,042
<i>was about a month before she died.</i>

215
00:17:35,127 --> 00:17:36,406
Miyuki-chan...

216
00:17:39,046 --> 00:17:42,806
Do you have katsuobushi?

217
00:17:59,130 --> 00:18:00,523
Bon apetit.

218
00:18:23,931 --> 00:18:26,781
This taste is just...

219
00:18:32,395 --> 00:18:34,040
Master.

220
00:18:35,452 --> 00:18:37,219
Thank you so much.

221
00:18:38,115 --> 00:18:40,649
Uh? For what?

222
00:18:41,881 --> 00:18:46,656
If I hadn't come to this place,

223
00:18:47,008 --> 00:18:51,064
I would have never gotten the chance
to experience so much happiness.

224
00:18:52,443 --> 00:18:55,275
No words can express
how thankful I am.

225
00:19:06,049 --> 00:19:09,479
Should I have one as well?

226
00:19:10,249 --> 00:19:11,465
Can you?

227
00:19:11,825 --> 00:19:13,585
Yeah.

228
00:19:22,419 --> 00:19:24,765
It's not that cold.
Is it all right with you?

229
00:19:25,401 --> 00:19:26,663
Yeah.

230
00:19:49,156 --> 00:19:51,320
Remember Chu-san?

231
00:19:51,515 --> 00:19:54,137
The one who bought your CD.

232
00:19:54,164 --> 00:19:58,216
He always said that he'd get
your autograph next time you come,

233
00:19:58,365 --> 00:20:01,485
so, sorry if I ask,
but will you...

234
00:20:19,235 --> 00:20:23,704
~ Closed for the Day ~

235
00:20:29,088 --> 00:20:31,729
I never expected it to happen
to someone as popular as she was.

236
00:20:31,903 --> 00:20:36,073
Miyuki-chan really made it big.

237
00:20:37,760 --> 00:20:40,385
She was the Miyuki-chan from this place.

238
00:20:40,605 --> 00:20:43,365
The one we knew...

239
00:20:44,996 --> 00:20:47,015
Wherever fate leads you.

240
00:20:47,040 --> 00:20:50,190
Wherever it leads your life to.

241
00:20:50,544 --> 00:20:55,314
From your childhood
to your adulthood...

242
00:20:56,251 --> 00:21:00,031
it is wherever fate
leads you to, indeed.

243
00:21:01,768 --> 00:21:03,615
It was quite the peculiar song,

244
00:21:03,827 --> 00:21:06,907
but it sure suited Miyuki-chan.

245
00:21:09,216 --> 00:21:14,296
You said something strange
happened this morning, Master?

246
00:21:16,355 --> 00:21:20,362
~ Chidori Miyuki ~
Bravely Fights Illness Until Death

247
00:22:00,083 --> 00:22:01,151
Miyuki-chan.

248
00:22:08,407 --> 00:22:10,587
Glad you came.

249
00:22:16,691 --> 00:22:20,594
~ To be continued ~

250
00:22:26,742 --> 00:22:29,545
With katsuobushi, it's always
better to scrape it fresh.

251
00:22:29,624 --> 00:22:32,804
But these days you don't
quite get the chance, do you?

252
00:22:34,060 --> 00:22:36,340
Look at that!

253
00:22:59,037 --> 00:22:59,690
I knew it!

254
00:22:59,803 --> 00:23:01,456
This must be the best way to do it.

255
00:23:01,689 --> 00:23:03,579
Good night everyone.

